Rating: 4
I made a few changes and used this recipe as a marinade. It was amazing. Peeled a whole head of garlic and threw it in a mini food-processor with a bit of olive oil and salt. Then I added about two tbs of fresh rosemary leaves and chopped it all till it was creamy. Finally, I added the juice of one lemon and enough olive oil to make the marinade a good consistency. I marinaded several peeled jumbo shrimps, tuna kabobs, and chicken tenders for about an hour. Grilled this and served it with roasted corn on the cob and grilled zucchini -- delicious. Next time I would add more rosemary and a bit less salt. Try this as a marinade! If I can force myself to follow a recipe, I might try to use this as a rub/paste -- I assume that's why a previous reviewer said it's messy?

