I made a low-fat, low-sodium version of this dish that has gotten RAVE reviews each of the 4 times I've prepared it for guests. For the marinade, I substituted fresh lemon and lime juice for the oil (3 whole lemons, 2 whole limes), left out the salt, and kept everything else the same -- well, maybe a bit more rosemary (yum!). I marinated frozen, peeled, jumbo shrimp overnight in this concoction (just put it in a Ziploc bag in the refrigerator and they'll thaw by morning). Skewer and broil... but watch carefully because they cook quickly! The shrimp turn out tangy and tender, and definitely not too salty!

